# Node.js + Express + JWT Backend Standards

## Tech Stack
- Backend: Node.js with Express.js 
- Authentication: JSON Web Tokens (JWT) 
- Version Control: Git 

## Strategy

### Strategic Planning with Pseudocode
- Begin each feature with detailed pseudocode
- Provide pseudocode for complex processes before coding
- Outline API endpoints and business logic clearly

## Code Quality
- Ensure secure, efficient code following RESTful API best practices
- Implement proper error handling and input validation
- Use middleware for cross-cutting concerns (auth, validation, logging)

## API Design
- Follow RESTful conventions
- Use proper HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)
- Return consistent response format
- Implement proper status codes

## Authentication Flow
- Use JWT for stateless authentication
- Implement token generation and verification
- Protect routes with authentication middleware
- Handle token expiry and refresh

## Error Handling
- Implement centralized error handling
- Return structured error responses
- Log errors with appropriate context
- Never expose sensitive information in errors

## Security Best Practices
- Validate all user inputs
- Use prepared statements / parameterized queries
- Implement rate limiting
- Use HTTPS in production
- Hash passwords with bcrypt
- Sanitize user data
